            <title>[SPARK-37004] Job cancellation causes py4j errors on Jupyter due to pinned thread mode</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-37004</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Spark 3.2.0 turned on py4j pinned thread mode by default (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-35303&quot; title=&quot;Enable pinned thread mode by default&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-35303&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-35303&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). However, in a jupyter notebook, after I cancel (interrupt) a long-running Spark job, the next Spark command will fail with some py4j errors. See attached notebook for repro.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cannot reproduce the issue after I turn off pinned thread mode .&lt;/p&gt;</description>
